               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa ṭomār “Book of the Letter (from Heaven)” (fols. 3r-16vb)
                     II) Śǝrʿāta faws manfasāwi “Order of Spiritual Medicine” (fols. 16vb-20rb),
                     unidentified 
 
 Additiones 1-2.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The columns are of different width due to inconsistent ruling: e.g.,
                        fols. 3, 4, 11v, 18.</note>
                     <note>- Text II (different from the work Maṣḥafa faws Manfasawi) is contained
                        also in Mss.<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdz011">DZ-011</ref>,<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESgms013">GMS-013</ref>.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="Codex">
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           <material key="parchment"/>
                        </support>
                        <extent>Made of <measure unit="leaf">20.0</measure> folios, in <measure unit="quire">4.0</measure> quires (A+3). <dimensions type="outer">
                              <height unit="mm">160</height>
                              <width unit="mm">140</width>
                              <depth unit="mm">15</depth>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation/>
                        <collation>
                           <list>
                              <item xml:id="q1">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">2</dim>
                                 <locus from="1r" to="2v"/>A(2/fols. 1r-2v) </item>
                              <item xml:id="q2">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">10</dim>
                                 <locus target="#10"/>
                                 <locus from="3r" to="12v"/> I(10/fols. 3r-12v) </item>
                              <item xml:id="q3">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">2</dim>
                                 <locus from="13r" to="14v"/> II(2/fols. 13r-14v) </item>
                              <item xml:id="q4">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">6</dim>
                                 <locus from="15r" to="20v"/> III(6/fols. 15r-20v).</item>
                           </list>
                        </collation>
                        <condition key="deficient">The Ms. has been resewn with a thread of vegetal
                           origin and the sewing has been crudely repaired with recent synthetic
                           threads.
 Both boards and the fols. are of irregular shape.
                              <locus target="#10">10</locus> is made out of two pieces of parchment.
                           
 Most of the fols. are affected by humidity; passages of the text on
                              <locus target="#8rb">8rb</locus>, 10va are hardly legible due to water
                           damage. 
 Cuts carefully amended on fols. 5, 10.
 A hole on
                              <locus target="#10">10</locus>.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="2" writtenLines="15">
                           <dimensions unit="mm">
                              <height>95</height>
                              <width>110</width>
                              <dim type="intercolumn">12</dim>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="margin">
                              <dim type="top">15</dim>
                              <dim type="bottom">48</dim>
                              <dim type="right">12</dim>
                              <dim type="left">15</dim>
                              <dim type="intercolumn">12</dim>
                           </dimensions>
                           <note/>
                           <ab type="ruling">14-15 lines on <locus from="11v" to="12r">11v-12r</locus>; 20 lines on <locus target="#5va">5va</locus>,
                              10rb</ab>
                           <ab type="pricking">Pricking and ruling are visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling" subtype="pattern"> Ruling pattern:
                              1A-1A-1A1A/0-0/0-0/C.</ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Primary pricks are partly visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Ruling pricks are visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The upper line is written above the ruling. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The bottom line is written above the ruling.</ab>
                           
                           <ab type="ruling"> The ruling is very inconsistent (fols. 3, 4, 11v,
                              18).</ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The scribe very often disregarded the ruling (e.g.
                                 <locus target="#11r">11r</locus>, 13r).</ab>
                        </layout>
                        
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Poor and crude, conspicuously angular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black and red (deep reddish brown).</seg>The scribe seems to
                        be the same as the one of MHG-005.<date>18th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; a few lines on the incipit page of
                           Texts I, II, and on fol. 11ra; names of the owners (fols. 10va, 16va);
                           elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Distinctive
                        features:</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> - the loops of the 5th vowel marker
                        are usually
                        open;</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic"> - the loop of ል is always
                        open.</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic"> - ዕ , ኢ, ኀ have a long horizontal
                        stroke on the
                        top;</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h6" script="Ethiopic"> - the vowel marker of እ is parallel to
                        the baseline of the
                        script;</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h7" script="Ethiopic"> - some letters have clumsy,
                        unproportionate shape: s. ሎ with large vowel marker (<locus target="#16vb">16vb</locus> l. 7); twisted ራ (<locus target="#6ra">6ra</locus> l.
                        7).</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#20r">f. 20r</locus>
                           <desc>: Ownership note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#20r">20r</locus>: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ የአባ፡ &lt;…&gt;ታ፡ ጽድቅ፡
                              ነው.</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> The note is written in the upper margin of the
                           fol.; it is partly written in Amharic and mentions ʾabbā<note>
                              &lt;…&gt;ta Ṣǝdǝq as the owner of the manuscript. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#00"/>
                           <desc> </desc>
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#20r">20r</locus>: Hymn to the Virgin Mary,
                              incomplete.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"> <locus target="#20r">20r</locus>: ኵሎሙ፡ ሠራዊተ፡
                              መላእክት፡ ይሴብሑኪ፡ ዘእምቅድመ፡ አለም፡ ህልዎትኪ፡ …</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> The hymn is identical to EMML 1593 (s. EMML V, 78)
                           and to MHG-001 (<locus target="#4ra">4ra-</locus>
                           <note>vb). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Erasures: <locus target="#10ra">10ra</locus>, 11rb,
                           14va, 15va, 19ra.
 - Corrections written over erased words and
                           passages, e.g.: <locus target="#6vb">6vb</locus>, 19va.
 - Omitted
                           letters written interlineally: <locus target="#7va">7va</locus>, 12va,
                           13ra, 14va.
 - Notes for the most part washed out and illegible:
                              <locus target="#10v">10v</locus>, 11r.
 - Writing exercises, minor
                           notes, doodles in black or red ink, in a blue pen or in pencil: <locus from="1r" to="2v">1r-2v</locus>, 4r-5r, 7r, 8r, 9r, 10v-11v,
                           20r-v.
 - Pen trial: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 1v.
 - Crude
                           doodles of human heads in black or red ink: <locus target="#2v">2v</locus>, 12v, 15r, 16r.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="partly">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two leather boards.
 Three sewing
                           stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="leather"/>
                        </decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Endbands"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Other"/>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
